To answer some:

Q: So what's with the new feature when you move up a rank you have to start over by choosing a path?! I had to start my brute from level 1 again because I won a tournament, how come? What's the purpose behind it?

A: I guess that's how the game works now. You start over at level 1 with a higher rank. You can also choose to get the same skills as you level up or completely randomize them in hopes of getting a better build.

Q: why isn't my brute ready the day after i use it?

A: Most likely this is because of the time-zone you're in. I'm not sure what time exactly do brutes get their fights available again, but if it's midnight for example.. it might be that when it's midnight at your place it's actually 10~11pm at their server location (thus the day is not over yet for them)

On june 11, 2011
Cripto
I have a question:

My brute has the weapons sai and knife. She also has the powers hurceulean strength, net and survival -

A) I've noticed the sai almost always make the player lose his/her weapon, and the knife hits multiple times. Will getting powers like "Fist of Fury/Tornado of Blows", or "Impact/Knock" increase the capabilities of my Sai and Knife, or will they have no effect on their weapon disarming ability, and multiple hits ability?

B) Are skills more important than stats? Or are stats more important than skills? Or both are equally important?

C) I've noticed that characters that have high agility or speed usually do better in higher levels. Is this true?

D) What skills should I get for my brute that are worth having? Any suggestion on stats?

E) What are good weapons to look for? Is there anything I need to know when wielding one? For example, when I owned a Bumps on my other brute, he did horrible every time he brought it out. Never hit anything, and was really slow with it. Do certain stats compliment certain weapons?

A) Yes. Many other weapons go hand in hand with the brutes stat and skill and could enhance the effect.

B) It depends. Skills and stats can go hand in hand. Some skills enhance the effect of the stats.

For example, a brute with high agility would become even more effective if it has the ability untouchable. The effect of immortality would be even greater when coupled with armour or extra thick skin, etc.

This is the same with weapons as well. Some weapons that have a particular ability, would be enhanced by a skill or stat. They are all as important as each, if you ask me. It's only that at a low level, it's just hard to see the effect of a lot of skills.


C) Well, in the lower levels, agility and speed tend to be so low that it becomes rather insignificant. But by the time the brute reaches a high level, the speed and agility would have had the time to increase to a level that would really show its effect in battles.

D) Skills you should look out for are:

Hammer - It bypasses all the opponents defences, whether it is a shield, a counter ability or a weapon with a counter ability. A brute with this skill runs to the opponent, carries them up into the air like superman and slams them on the ground, thus dealing a great amount of damage.

Resistant - A good defence skills that can even reduce the damage inflicted by a brute with the hammer skill. If damage dealt against a brute with this skill is above 20, it is reduced. Very effective against high damage capable weapons. Could be a life saver.

Martial arts - Even when you have no weapon. You can deal a great amount of damage on your opponent.

Bomb - A brute with this ability can throw bombs at the opponent that, from observation, seems to inflict damage around 23 HP points. The brute has the ability to use this twice, unlike the first version. This is very good against an opponent with animals because not only would it kill them (except the bear), it simultaneously inflicts the same amount of damage on your opponent. I would say it is the best counter against animals, but others could disagree and might say hypnosis , or net is.

Immortality - It is basically a doped up version of vitality(the more common one). Immortality gives your brute a lot of hp points, making them extremely hard to kill.

Armour - Reduces the damage you take by a lot. Basically a doped up version of extra thick skin

First Strike - Very useful for me. Not only do you get to strike first against an opponent, but you get to strike again. The skill basically gives you a bonus strike at the beginning of every match, if the other brute does not have the same ability.

Determination - This is very useful if you have weapons that are low in accuracy, like bumps. If a brute with this skill attacks another brute and misses, it has a high chance of attacking again until he deals damage.

Untouchable - Has a high probability of evading the opponents attacks. From observation, it is better at higher levels.


E) Good weapons to look for are:

Shuriken - Most effective when it is your only or last weapon. Overall, it inflicts a similar amount of damage as the 'sword' only that it is divided into about a billion throws. So the power could range from any amount less than 10, to something, say - 40 on average. It is better than one strike weapons that deal a similar amount of damage, because if it misses, the whole 40 hp damage that could have been inflicted is then lost. However, the shuriken is almost guaranteed to inflict damage, whether it is the minimum possible, or the maximum possible.

Sai - Doped up knife, in the sense that it is around the same size but seems to attack either as many or more times, inflicts a similar amount of damage, but has the added effect of knocking away your opponent's weapon

Whip - It seems to have the highest percentage of countering an opponents attack before they hit you. Also, unlike other long weapons like: Baton, Lance, Trident and Halberd, the whip allows to counter against even other long weapons before it hits you. Normally, the counter ability that the long weapons have is nullified against other long weapons.

norby89
There have been cases where I have seen the bar at it's absolute lowest on a brute with very low health (60-70 range) and their survival skill would still activate on the next attack, even though the health bar does not go down at all.
Survival will always activate on a fatal blow, even if that means that the players health is reduced with 0 HP.

There are also cases where people have such a thin health bar that it goes below the amount that the skill survival allows a brute to retain.
That all depends on the player's health, players with Vitality or Immortal will appear to have a really thin health bar when Survival kicks in. That doesn't mean their health is below 1 though.

Determination or Relentless?
A permanent 30% chance to successfully hit is better than a 70% chance to strike again just to miss and strike again and miss, pretty soon It's a 70% chance of a 70% chance of a 70% chance and your odds have become very small of connecting with a successful hit. Relentless

On august 21, 2011
[None]
Toughened Skin or 3 Strength?
Well in my opinion your greatest feature is clearly the flail. The only thing you really need to do is draw it in a battle. You want to prolong your life as long as possible (which is why vitality is useful for later, I would hope you will get more +3 endurance chances). +3 Strength would really only help with defeating your opponents before you draw your flail, whereas toughened skin would buy you some more time to draw it out. If you did not have vitality and I didn't expect you to have a lot of Health later on, I would suggest Strength. However, it looks like health won't be a problem so I highly suggest toughened skin.

Toughened Skin

Timinator
My low level brute has back-up and now i leveled up and offered back-up. whom shall i back things up? o_o answers are appreciated.
A brute with Backup can only help brutes that are of equal of lower level. So if your Backup brute is level 10, it won't help any brutes on your account that are level 9 or lower.

What increases the damage of noodle bowl? Agility, Speed, Strength?
According to guides I've seen, strength does not increase the damage of throwing weapons (such as the Noodle Bowl), but agility takes that role instead. My experiences are consistent with this theory. Speed does not ever increase damage, only frequency of attacks.
On august 22, 2011
Timinator
Lightning Bolt or +3 endurance
Lightning Bolt without a doubt. Always choose stat-increasing skills over individual stats, as they will help a lot more in the long-run. (the +50% counts toward all future points in that stat as well)

+3 Endurance for you means +16 Health
Not quite, it means +18 health (6 x 3 = 18, not 16).

So you'd have 90-91 HP if you went with endurance, not 88.

On august 24, 2011
[None]
When you level up and one of those two options appear,
The long sword (more damage) will always appear as "Sword"
The shorter sword (less damage) will always appear as "Broadsword"

You will never be allowed to choose between Sword and Broadsword on the same level up.
You are always given a +stat option per level

Hello and welcome to the game.
Yes - IF you rank up - then you would be reset to level 1 and you would be able to 1. choose same destiny - if you wrote down your choices and you will make the EXACT same choices on levelups in next rank - you will get the same skills/weapons. If you choose change destiny (new destiny) - your brute will be higher rank but the choices would be totally random - he may get beter choices or worse...

But if you dont want to be reset to lev1 and levelup again - you can just not rank up when you win a tourney (after you win a turney there will be link to take your brute up rank - just dont click it) (but then you wont be able to enter turney again) or just not enter turneys - it is not obligatory to enter them

RuleOfThumb
sorry i didn't think it was a question... as an answer to you: tough luck... as it seems the system doesn't count shield block with diminishing returns (if you block your average chance decreases, if you don't then it increases because the system opts to have the initial 45% chance value to be true on the long run) instead counts every attack as a singular equation where you have 45% chance to block, gets a result and at the next attack it stats the sequence from top. this can be the reason for unrealistic blocking rates on some brutes (plus or minus).
hope i could make clear the difference between singular and diminishing chance calculation

for low chance you saw your brute enough times, but for the contrary here is an example:
http://mybrute.muxxu.com/fight/7118593?c hk=4a86
the brute on the right side was mine long time ago but i deleted it because it sucked. 13 consecutive blocks right before my brute throws away the whip (ofc broadsword included what gives around 15% block rate also, but if it would be diminishing calculation then with 60% block rate he should have received 5 hits and block 8 from the 13)

On october 31, 2011
Demonology
jengas -
For me - if you have to get a few bad weapons in order to get a good weapon and skill - I would change the destiny. Because in long run (higher ranks, higher levels - better oponents) it would hurt you a lot.

And weapons like broadsword and knife can get pretty good - if you get some good skills later on (like shield, weapons master, fists of furry, hostility, 6th sense) - they are pretty avesome!
So FROM MY POINT OF VIEW - if I have to get broadsword (happened a few times actually) to get something better - I will do that and do not change the destiny. But for other bad weapons - I wouldnt put an effort into such brute.

As for skills - it is a bit different. Actually I can think of a skill that can "spoil" your brute. Some are better some are not that good. But nothing that would hurt you badly in the long run. In contrary to weapons - if you get a bad weapon: each time the brute draws it you would whish that he had chosen any of the 3-5 great weapons that you managed to collect during levelups. So - if I have a brute that gets a few lame skills and then gets something great - I would keep it.

And if a brute does not get the good weapon untill level 5-7 it is really hard to level him up - but in some cases it is worth it - because then you see how he rocks at higher levels!

So a quick summary:
you get a few bad weapons to get something good => BAD IDEA!
you get a few bad skills to get something good => OK. If you dont mind the pain of levfelling through them on each new rank or plan to stay one rank
you get nothing special untill level10 - BAD IDEA, I would change the destiny. Even if on lev 10 you get something amazing - your brute wont get from bad to freaking-avesome in one levelup - it is a combo of skills/weapons/stats that count - so you would still have 10 levelups to cath up to the best brutes...



And - 6th sense is a verry good skill! Why would you consder it bad?

On january 30, 2012
benwhitfield
armor, shield, counter attack, martial arts, hypnosis. probably some of the best in the game. it's all a matter of opinion though, and what kind of brute you have. if he's gifted with feline agility, you may want to look out for weapons that hit several times in one attack. herculean strength brutes you may want to look at flails, brutes with speed you definitely want the knife along for the ride since knife boosts the speed of a brute.

certain skills go well with others. a brute with a shield will cherish the day they get counter attack and weapons master, since both skills will boost broadsword, scimitar, sword, halberd, and knife. strength and martial arts will win fights by itself, but pair it with shock and you have a brute that can go toe-to-toe with most any.

throwing weapons need agility to boost damage dealt, and speed will help prevent your opponent from attack for a long time, allowing you to avoid damage or loosing your throwing weapon to a shock/sabotage brute.

try to avoid recon skill. you'll have great speed but your opponent gets 2-4 attacks before you do anything. you may consider this skill if you have great defense, lightning bolt already, and especially first strike. keep in mind first strike gets you and extra attack and allows you to punch/bash them first, so if you get recon you will be going back to almost even initiative with your opponent.

low health brutes need some kind of defensive skill or an awesome offense to end fights quickly.

i'm leaving quite a few details out, it may be best to come back and give brute details and ask for advice as you are offered a skill. this game is trial and error, so even if you get a few bad level ups you may be able to search out different choices to build a great brute
